1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,202
{\an8}What seems to be the problem?

2
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:38,496
{\an8}- Sir.
- What’s happening with the two of you?

3
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:40,373
{\an8}We have to remove Alex from this case.

4
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:41,958
{\an8}If we’re going to count contributions,

5
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:44,836
{\an8}every breakthrough
in this case came from me.

6
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:58,349
{\an8}I know it’s bothering you,

7
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:01,895
{\an8}<i>those consecutive attacks</i>
<i>of the Moravianos.</i>

8
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:06,900
{\an8}And if you think we’re just going
to stand here and accept their attacks?

9
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:09,944
{\an8}It’s time to strike back.

10
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,865
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

11
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:23,124
{\an8}I prepared a file for the operation.

12
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:24,793
{\an8}All the details are in there,

13
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:26,169
{\an8}so study it carefully.

14
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:28,421
{\an8}And if you have any questions,

15
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:30,089
{\an8}do not hesitate to talk to me.

16
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:32,175
{\an8}Is that understood?

17
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:33,718
{\an8}- Copy.
- Yes, ma'am.

18
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,853
{\an8}How long are you going
to give me the silent treatment?

19
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:46,606
{\an8}You're like my classmate
back in grade 1, Barry Gonsales.

20
00:01:46,689 --> 00:01:48,942
{\an8}He got mad at me
because I spelled Gonsales wrong.

21
00:01:49,025 --> 00:01:50,693
{\an8}I used "Z" instead of "S".

22
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:54,823
{\an8}Okay.

23
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:57,700
{\an8}I know I haven't been myself lately,

24
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:59,077
{\an8}and I'll admit

25
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,745
{\an8}I've gotten attached to Mikoy.

26
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:03,248
{\an8}But it's not because of what you think.

27
00:02:06,918 --> 00:02:07,752
{\an8}Because, you know,

28
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:09,587
{\an8}I'm the one who got him involved in this.

29
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:11,589
{\an8}I really want to bring
the Moravianos down,

30
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:14,592
{\an8}but not at the expense
of someone else's life.

31
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:16,594
{\an8}Bok, I won't be able to handle it

32
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:19,305
{\an8}if another innocent life
is lost because of me.

33
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,975
{\an8}Maybe this kind of thinking

34
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,435
{\an8}clouds my judgment, like you said.

35
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:28,398
{\an8}Sianong, I need you.

36
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:32,026
{\an8}So, Bok, whatever this is,
please stop already.

37
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:34,195
{\an8}Please?

38
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:02,932
{\an8}Why?

39
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:04,726
Is this about Chiara?

40
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:06,811
What did Brusko say?

41
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:09,856
He didn't say anything.

42
00:03:11,816 --> 00:03:13,902
But I know it's about Mikoy.

43
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:15,737
Chiara is hurt.

44
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:18,072
Because of him.

45
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:20,491
Mikoy? I don't get it.

46
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,368
What did Mikoy do? Cheat on her?

47
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:24,662
Cheat with a guy? I don't know.

48
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,664
Why did he hurt Chiara?

49
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:28,082
I don't get it.

50
00:03:31,502 --> 00:03:34,255
I know it might sound impossible,

51
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,424
but it seems like Mikoy

52
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,761
has bigger and darker secrets than that.

53
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:55,401
La Morte Bianca is not happy.

54
00:03:57,779 --> 00:03:59,530
She has sent the Painter.

55
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:02,617
Painter?

56
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,702
The mansion still looks fine though.

57
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:05,912
Yes.

58
00:04:05,995 --> 00:04:08,039
Our color scheme still looks beautiful.

59
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:11,042
- Though the bathroom--
- Not that kind of painter.

60
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:18,091
The one who can paint our walls

61
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:19,509
bloody red.

62
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,242
Dad.

63
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,036
Mikoy.

64
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,248
I let you meet your handler last night.

65
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,125
Even by yourself.

66
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:55,420
I also didn't ask you what happened

67
00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:57,046
or for an explanation.

68
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:00,008
But I'm not naive.

69
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:04,345
I notice a lot of things.

70
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,681
Especially when

71
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,684
you couldn't answer your mother's question

72
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,185
about how Chiara was doing.

73
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:14,188
Is something going on?

74
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,485
It's nothing, Dad.

75
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:23,031
There was just an emergency
at the agency last night,

76
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:25,325
but it had nothing to do with my mission.

77
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:26,576
Liar.

78
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:30,330
I can tell you're lying.

79
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:36,210
Come on, Dad.

80
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:38,963
I already told you last night,
and I'll say it again.

81
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:41,424
I don't want you getting involved
in the mess I got into.

82
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:44,719
Dad, just leave me be.

83
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,971
Trouble is normal in missions.

84
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:50,516
That's why what you need

85
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,102
is a reliable partner

86
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:54,520
like me.

87
00:05:58,274 --> 00:05:59,358
Boys!

88
00:05:59,442 --> 00:06:03,071
I'm heading to the market.
Do you boys have any requests?

89
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:05,656
Anything you want me to buy?

90
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,242
Like ideas for a dish?
So I can buy the ingredients.

91
00:06:13,414 --> 00:06:14,874
Just fresh coconut juice, Mom.

92
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:16,584
Okay. How about you, dear?

93
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:17,585
Later.

94
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:19,921
Later, Tess.

95
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:23,091
We're discussing something important.

96
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:24,926
Is that so?

97
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:29,639
Okay, request granted. Dear,

98
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:31,307
I'll see you later!

99
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:35,895
Trust me, son, I'm the only one
you can rely on right now.

100
00:06:36,687 --> 00:06:38,064
Oh my!

101
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,025
That’s what I’m talking about.

102
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:43,528
I forgot my wallet again.

103
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:45,488
You're getting forgetful again, Tess.

104
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,243
What do you mean by that?

105
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:54,580
And why do you seem
so confident about this mission?

106
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,749
Are you still hiding
something from me, Dad?

107
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:57,917
And were you really

108
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,128
just an intelligence asset
for law enforcement before,

109
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,213
like what you told me the other night?

110
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:11,264
Is this my final hour?

111
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,103
Dad?

112
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:21,107
And you still haven't explained

113
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:23,443
why you have so many hidden guns, Dad!

114
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,781
I'll only tell you this.

115
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:31,409
This is top secret, okay?

116
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:33,786
Okay, Dad.

117
00:07:34,787 --> 00:07:36,414
I was part of a…

118
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:38,499
kill squad.

119
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:43,463
A clandestine operative
in a top military unit.

120
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:45,798
Like…

121
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,383
Naruto's ANBU?

122
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,010
Like that?

123
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,973
Mikoy, I have some very special skills.

124
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:58,561
I was the best ANBU you're talking about.

125
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:03,691
And my name isn't Mario.

126
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,696
- I am known as…
- Dad.

127
00:08:10,364 --> 00:08:13,618
Isidro Catacutan.

128
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:17,580
The Butuan Executioner of Butuan.

129
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:24,378
Butuan Executioner of Butuan?

130
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:25,505
Yes.

131
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,549
I never back down.

132
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,760
No one can make me tremble,

133
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:32,053
no matter who they are.

134
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:39,852
Honey!

135
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:42,188
What are you doing there?
You've been chatting too much.

136
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:45,358
- Aren't you coming to the market with me?
- All right.

137
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,194
I'll carry the bags.

138
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:49,779
Okay, okay.

139
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,032
Remember.

140
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:56,869
The Executioner of Butuan.

141
00:08:58,829 --> 00:09:01,499
- Mario! You’re still chatting!
- Okay, okay, I'm coming.

142
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,044
The Executioner.

143
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:08,381
- I’m telling you, time is running out!
- All right, I’m going to carry the bag!

144
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,136
You know, I watched <i>Lord of the Rings</i>,

145
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,680
the director’s cut.

146
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:19,642
That’s when I realized
Sam is the real protagonist of the story.

147
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:21,644
All this time, I thought it was Frodo.

148
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,021
How about you? What do you think?

149
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,982
Are you in Aragorn's camp?

150
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:28,109
Bro, keep the change.

151
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,200
Are you still upset?

152
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:38,536
Okay, fine, be that way.

153
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:41,247
Just keep your eyes open.

154
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:43,541
We are looking for Quebec Romero 1020.

155
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:45,501
That’s the plate number
of the container van.

156
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:49,338
And if Mikoy is right,
that will take us to the secret hideout.

157
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,426
And may I just remind you

158
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:54,885
that you’re violating habit number five

159
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,471
of <i>Seven Habits</i>
<i>of Highly Effective People</i>.

160
00:09:58,055 --> 00:09:59,307
Get it?

161
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:02,101
Seek to understand, then to be understood.

162
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:05,479
The habit that forces you
to understand the fears, needs,

163
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,315
and the perspective of the other person.

164
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:11,944
I just wanted to protect the people
who’s important to me, Sianong.

165
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:16,157
And if you were in Mikoy’s situation,
I’d do the same for you.

166
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:25,374
I wish you would see my intentions
and understand why I'm doing this.

167
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,087
That’s our truck.

168
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,093
Eagle Two, target location confirmed.

169
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:39,930
Copy that, Mother Eagle.

170
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:40,931
Dara.

171
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:15,091
Ouch. Mario, wait.
I can't take it anymore.

172
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:16,634
I can't take it anymore.
I really need to pee.

173
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:25,976
Mikoy, I'm telling the truth.

174
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,270
I can still help you.

175
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:29,855
Dad!

176
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:31,524
Are you joking again?

177
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:33,150
I'm not joking.

178
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,985
I can still fight.

179
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,946
Look at my moves.

180
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:38,739
Up. Cross.

181
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:42,618
See?

182
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:43,786
Wait.

183
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,871
- Why?
- It hurts.

184
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,249
- See, Dad, that's what I was saying.
- Ouch.

185
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:49,959
- Ouch. What is this?
- Mom!

186
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:51,836
What happened, Mario?

187
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,379
- I don't know.
- What happened?

188
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:55,965
I forgot to tell you earlier,
I went to the gym.

189
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:58,759
I worked out. I lifted around 350 kilos.

190
00:11:58,843 --> 00:11:59,844
I did 50 reps.

191
00:12:00,928 --> 00:12:03,139
- Wow.
- I think something gave out.

192
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:04,598
- Fifty…
- Rotator cuff…

193
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,685
Fifty reps? Fifty reps
carrying vegetables maybe.

194
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:09,854
Okay, help…

195
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:12,189
Help your father. I'll just get some oil.

196
00:12:12,773 --> 00:12:13,941
Yes, Mom.

197
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:17,695
Are you really okay, Dad?

198
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,531
- Of course.
- All right, Dad, I believe you now.

199
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,199
You don't need to do that anymore.

200
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,702
But that doesn't mean
I'll agree with what you want,

201
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:26,203
that I'll still let you do it.

202
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:28,247
Why are you so stubborn?

203
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:30,249
Why don't you want to ask for help?

204
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,877
Because I've already
made my decision, Dad.

205
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:35,087
I'm going to tell Chiara everything.

206
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:37,256
Instead of stressing myself out,

207
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:39,842
I should be true to her, right?

208
00:12:40,551 --> 00:12:42,011
It's time for her to know

209
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:43,762
about everything I've been doing.

210
00:14:30,452 --> 00:14:32,746
The site is 12 clicks from our position.

211
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:34,915
The hideout has three entry points.

212
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:36,667
There's entry 1.

213
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:41,922
{\an8}<i>Entry 2.</i>

214
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:49,346
{\an8}<i>And entry 3.</i>

215
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,931
{\an8}Security is lighter than expected.

216
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:52,808
But let's assume it's a trap.

217
00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:59,023
- Copy, ma'am.
- Now move.

218
00:14:59,106 --> 00:14:59,940
Move.

219
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:33,599
Well, now

220
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,559
I know.

221
00:16:24,858 --> 00:16:25,776
Hold.

222
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,241
What do you want

223
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:34,702
We are the Global Agency
for Government Operations,

224
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,370
and we have a search warrant.

225
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:38,956
May I see it?

226
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:58,142
Cover!

227
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,902
Clear! Move!

228
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,825
You're being careless, Viktor.

229
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:16,410
Extremely careless.

230
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:19,538
And your security team? Stupid.

231
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:22,166
They don't know what they're doing.

232
00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:24,418
That's why I can take them all down.

233
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:28,130
No wonder La Morte is unhappy with you.

234
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:27,523
Is it because you're that old

235
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:30,400
that you've forgotten all your failures,

236
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,318
Viktor?

237
00:19:06,436 --> 00:19:08,188
You're no longer

238
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:10,440
the Valtrovi I remember.

239
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,059
Ridiculous.

240
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:22,846
Get down, Bok!

241
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:29,686
Let's go, Bok.

242
00:20:31,939 --> 00:20:34,024
Cover, Bok! Cover!

243
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:13,397
Mother Eagle, area 2 clear.

244
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,731
Copy that.

245
00:21:26,785 --> 00:21:27,786
Clear!

246
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:37,713
Move.

247
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:39,131
Move.

248
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:01,445
Bok.

249
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,156
Be careful.

250
00:22:08,535 --> 00:22:09,745
Go, go, go!

251
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,226
Open it.

252
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:43,820
<i>But you know?</i>

253
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,036
Don't!

254
00:23:05,592 --> 00:23:07,594
Alex!

255
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:24,194
I cannot believe
you fell into that honey trap.

256
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:26,071
Sir, I think it's Mikoy.

257
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:28,532
How much more evidence do we need

258
00:23:28,615 --> 00:23:30,075
before you realize
that what I'm saying is true,

259
00:23:30,158 --> 00:23:32,369
that Mikoy is compromised?

260
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:43,338
The Moravianos know
that you're an asset to the agency.

261
00:23:49,344 --> 00:23:52,180
<i>I’ll be the one to kill him!</i>

